[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    146[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m2[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mState-level confidentiality requirements vary.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Some states have additional behavioral-health confidentiality protections beyond 42 CFR Part 2 (mental-health-record confidentiality statutes, substance-use-disorder treatment record statutes, HIV/AIDS confidentiality statutes). The architecture does not specify how the per-state confidentiality regime is detected, applied, or audited.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    147[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    148[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m3[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe behavioral-health profile is named as supported but not architecturally specified.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe says "the architecture supports a behavioral-health profile that the institution can apply per visit type or per clinician" but does not specify what the profile does at the architecture level (which retention window applies, which access-control surface narrows, which consent flow is augmented, which patient-portal release path is gated, which audit-log discipline tightens).[K
